  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0dbb\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca \u0d86\u0db1\u0dba\u0db1\u0dba \u0d94\u0dc3\u0dca\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dda\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dad\u0dc4\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Australia bans Russian gold imports",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Australia will provide 34 additional armored vehicles to Ukraine, and the import of Russian gold will be banned, said Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese during an emergency visit to Ukraine.",
        "At a press conference in Kyiv with President Volodymyr Zelensky, Albanese said Australia would impose sanctions and travel bans on 16 more Russian ministers and oligarchs, bringing the total number of Russians sanctioned by Australia to 843.",
        "Also, as part of a new aid package worth USD 68 million, Albanese said that Ukraine will be provided with 20 Bushmasters and other technical equipment such as drones requested by Ukraine."
      ],
